<refentry id="bif.Log" xreflabel="Log">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>Log</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>Log</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>Log</refname>
<refpurpose>
Returns the natural logarithm of a number
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
Log[x->NUMBER] =: NUMBER 
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>Log</function>
computes the natural logarithm of <parameter>x</parameter>.  It is an error if
<parameter>x</parameter> is nonpositive.  The result is always in
floating-point precision, regardless of the precision of
<parameter>x</parameter>.
</para>
</refsect1>

